      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While the earnest money is secure in escrow, genuine disagreements can complicate things. Control over the funds rests with the escrow agent, who is obligated by the contract to follow the agreed-upon instructions. If a dispute arises, the escrow agent acts as a third-party custodian, often requiring instructions from both parties or potentially involving legal intervention if negotiations stall. It is designed to prevent either party from unilaterally taking the money before closing.",
